%N A392072 Smallest integer k such that 1 + x^2 + y^2 = k*prime(n) has at least one solution for some integers x, y.
%C A392072 We use a classic property of the sum of three squares: for any odd prime number p, there exist integers x, y, z such that 1 + x^2 + y^2 = z*p with 0 < z < p.
%C A392072 a(n) is the least k such that k*prime(n)-1 is in A001481. - _Robert Israel_, Jan 29 2026
%H A392072 Robert Israel, <a href="/A392072/b392072.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A392072 *---*------------*----------------------------*
%e A392072 | n | k | (x,y)  | 1 + x^2 + y^2 = k*prime(n) |
%e A392072 *---*------------*----------------------------*
%e A392072 | 1 | 1 | (0,1)  |  1 + 0^2 + 1*2 = 1*2       |
%e A392072 | 2 | 1 | (1,1)  |  1 + 1^2 + 1^2 = 1*3       |
%e A392072 | 3 | 1 | (0,2)  |  1 + 0^2 + 2^2 = 1*5       |
%e A392072 | 4 | 2 | (2,3)  |  1 + 2^2 + 3^2 = 2*7       |
%e A392072 | 5 | 1 | (1,3)  |  1 + 1^2 + 3^2 = 1*11      |
%e A392072 | 6 | 2 | (0,5)  |  1 + 0^2 + 5^2 = 2*13      |
%e A392072 | 7 | 1 | (0,4)  |  1 + 0^2 + 4^2 = 1*17      |
%e A392072 | 8 | 1 | (3,3)  |  1 + 3^2 + 3^2 = 1*19      |
%e A392072 | 9 | 2 | (3,6)  |  1 + 3^2 + 6^2 = 2*23      |
%e A392072 |10 | 5 | (0,12) |  1 + 0^2 + 12^2 =5*29      |
%p A392072 ss:= proc(s)
%p A392072   andmap(t -> t[1] mod 4 <> 3 or t[2]::even, ifactors(s)[2])
%p A392072 end proc:
%p A392072 f:= proc(n) local p,k;
%p A392072       p:= ithprime(n);
%p A392072       for k from 1 do if ss(k*p-1) then return k fi od;
%p A392072 end proc:
%p A392072 map(f,[$1..100]); # _Robert Israel_, Jan 29 2026
